{
  "stem": "6966.4",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I'm with 200 men who seem to be all right.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I used to be in a mo-- boxing club before the war, so I probably had the strong posture.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I was with 200 men selected to go to Monowitz.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Monowitz is another three miles away from Auschwitz, a big camp, 10,000 men.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The same life-- little food, beatings, hard work, unloading train loads with cement.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "One afternoon, our foreman said we're going to see how strong I am.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I carried 52 sacks of cement on my back-- 52 sacks from half past 2:00 till about quarter past 5:00.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that went on often, day after day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I remember once, you do the same thing, and you carry the cement to a lorry.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the lorry is connected with a board, a wooden board, another wooden board sitting in the middle.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So if you walk in the middle, you go up and down because it was too heavy, what I was carrying.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "One day, it fell off my back and split.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the Germans called it sabotage.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "The kapo used to hit me about it, yeah.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Another thing I did to, to fight my hunger is after my-- I received my half a liter or 3/4 liter soup in my own barrack, I used to wander out and go to the other barracks, go inside the other barracks, and ask the kapos, can I sing some songs for the prisoners?",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And if the kapo said yes, do it, three, four songs I sang.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And then if there was any soup left, they gave me some soup.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I did it three or four barracks to fight my hunger.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
